<figureCitation box="[957,1056,1699,1723]" captionStart="Figure 146-151" captionStartId="54.[192,276,1720,1742]" captionTargetBox="[272,1352,197,1635]" captionTargetId="figure-17@54.[269,1361,191,1647]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Figure 146-151. Male genitalia of Porphyrogenes; shown are lateral view of uncus, gnathos, tegumen, and saccus; dorsal view of uncus and tegumen; ventral view of uncus and gnathos; juxta; lateral view (with extended vesica) and often dorsal view of aedeagus; internal lateral view of right valva (inset shows the flattened harpe). 146) P. simulator, holotype, BOLIVIA (GTA 4181); 147) P. spadix, holotype, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 3894); 148) P. sparus (also including anterior view of harpe), holotype, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 3928); 149) P. specularis, holotype, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 3589); 150) P. spina, holotype, PANAMA (GTA 8905); 151) P. sporta, holotype, COLOMBIA (GTA 4180)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169724/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 146</figureCitation>
